insert into casemap_documents (id, kind, label, document_text, metadata) values ('case:yeung_may_wan_v_hksar', 'case', 'Yeung May Wan v HKSAR', 'Yeung May Wan v HKSAR The Basic Law of Hong Kong and the ICCPR limit the boundaries of these powers, and their exact scope is mostly detailed in the PFO. Once again, the statute books should be read alongside the common law, as exemplified by Yeung May Wan v HKSAR, the seminal Court of Final Appeal authority on the subject of how police power should be construed.80 4.1.1 Power of arrest [6-47] The main provision denoting the power of arrest of police officers is section 50(1...', '{"type": "case", "label": "Yeung May Wan v HKSAR", "keywords": ["police", "power", "arrest", "yeung", "wan", "hksar"]}'::jsonb) on conflict (id) do update set kind = excluded.kind, label = excluded.label, document_text = excluded.document_text, metadata = excluded.metadata;
